#Angular
Things we will learn in this program.
1.Components
2.Modules
3.Directives
4.Data Bindings
5.Pipes
6.Http Client
7.Routing

Question- Why Angular?
Answer- Following are the reasons we choose Angular:
Cross Browser Support
Typescript support
Web components
Mobile Application
Better Performance

=> Without refersing page => Single page Application(SPA)- without requesting a new page from the server we update part of the page.
Dynamically loads HTML content without refreshing.
Angular using JS/Typescript(recommended).

Angular is component based. Each component is independent.
Inside a component-
  1.Logic
  2.View


                              Root Component
                              /          \
            Child Component 1       Child Component 2
             /          \
Child Component 3     Child Component 4

Angular CLI =ng
Command to create a new project = ng new <project_name>
command to build and run on local = ng server --open 
command to create new component, directive, pip = ng generate <name>
command to build app = ng build



Folder structure in Angular :
node_modules = Node.js creates this folder and puts all the npm modules installed as listed in package.json.
src/ = All application related files will be stored inside it.
angular.json =  Angular cli config file.
package.json = node config file.
tsconfig.json = typescript configuration file


Question= What is component?
Answer = Basic building block.
         Separates concern
         Reuseable

Example = mCart component(Parent)
  Welcome Component(child)     Login Component(child)

import from '@angular/core'
@Component is the decorator

Example :
@Component({
  selector: 'app-login',
  templateUrl: './login.component.html',
  styleUrls: ['./login.component.css']
})
export class LoginComponent implements OnInit {
  userName:string = "";
  password:string = "";
}

